                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Regarding the origin and date of composition see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107145">Jönsson (1998)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="243" to="243" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl> (where Jönsson also argues that the fragment may have been written by one of Birgitta's confessors). The fragment was kept at <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100101">Vadstena</placeName>. From there it was transferred to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName> and subsenquently to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100006">Royal Swedish Academy of Letters, History and Antiquities</orgName>. In <date when="1854"/> the text was transferred to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName>. This fragment was previously bound together with A 65, which consist of two leaves of Birgitta's autograph. This leaf was removed and renamed A 65a at some point after <date when="1918"/>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
